# Cross-platform line-ending normalization (#139 — Windows port).
#
# ReCue is now developed on both Windows and macOS. Store every text file as
# LF in the repo and check it out as LF on all platforms, so a Windows checkout
# (where core.autocrlf would otherwise inject CRLF) can't break `cargo fmt
# --check` or `prettier --check` — both of which expect LF. macOS is unaffected
# (its working tree was already LF).
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets — never apply line-ending conversion.
*.png binary
*.ico binary
*.icns binary

# kanban-dev-pima pipeline: both files are append-only and are committed straight onto
# main by their lanes (plan -> ASSUMPTIONS.md, archive -> TASK_ARCHIVE.md) while the merge
# lane is landing PRs onto that same branch. `merge=union` keeps BOTH sides of a conflict,
# so no archive entry and no assumption is ever dropped to make a push go through.
TASK_ARCHIVE.md merge=union
ASSUMPTIONS.md  merge=union
